quish, the girl finds that nearly all hope is lost. It was the end of the road for her. The blade still in hand, Miriam grabs hold of the girl’s shirt and pulls her to her feet. Shoving her against a near by wall, Miriam presses the blade to her neck while fists full of fabric keep her pinned in place. <br>
<br>
“What’s your name”<br>
<br>
“Take anything you want. I have money, I have jewels, I’ll give you anything you want”<br>
<br>
“I want your name”<br>
<br>
“Please… please don’t hurt me” <br>
<br>
Was this slut stupid? NAME. GIVE YOUR NAME. A piece of scrap leather was pinned to the girl’s shirt. A nametag! How convenient! She must have just come from her night job, how fabulous. Unpinning the tag, Miriam reads it carefully out loud.<br>
<br>
“Caru. Hmmm, nice name. Oh wait! I think I know you! Tell me, Caru…” She spoke the name with bitterness and disgust, “You wouldn’t happen to know a guy named, oh lets see, Caelestis? Would you?”<br>
<br>
“Caelestis… He’s my boyfriend. How do you know his name?…” She was very scared, like a timid little rabbit. Her angelic voice was like nails scratching on a blackboard to Miriam. Miriam’s eye twitches and her ear is pressed against her shoulder. Boyfriend… boyfriend… boyfriend… boyfriend… boyfriend… boyfriend… boyfriend boyfriend boyfriend boyfriend boyfriend<br>
