RIEND BOY MOTHER @#%$ FRIEND!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Miriam closes her eyes a moment and takes the kind of breath one would take while trying to regain a grip on reality. Her mind had been more fragile since Caelestis proved she was nothing more than a side girl. Something to keep his bed warm when no one else would. The image of herself had been right… she * was * disgusting, she * was * weak… she was nothing. There were too many emotions, too many thoughts, too many feelings to shove into a bottle all at once, and her bottle was too small. Her stored memories, hidden emotions, denyed feelings, all explode with in the confines of her mind simultaneously. Her world was nothing more than a sheet of glass shattered into a million tiny grains of sand. Boyfriend…<br>
<br>
Caru’s scream shatters the still of the night. Again again again again again again again again!! The pin was shoved into her right eye again and again and again and again, until it finally got stuck on the pin. Moving it over an inch, Miriam shoves it deep within her left eye. Yanking it from her skull, Miriam now had both of Caru’s eyes on the pin. Blood gushes like two flash flooded rivers of life from the cavities that once held two crystal blue eyes. Caru’s scream was unwavering and quite annoying. Time to fix that. Pulling a finely sharpened sewing needle from her pocket, Miriam threads it with some string that she found in her wrist pouch. Time to end that annoying scream. Caru tries desperately to get her hands to her face, but Miriam puts her forearm against her neck and shoves away any attempt and putting pressure on the bleeding holes. Apparently the girl had some instincts, not enough to notice. Nails scratch blindly at Miriam’s upper torso and arms, her leather made nice whore scratch protection. <br>
<br>
“Stop moving, ya dumb bitch” <br>
<br>
Applying more pressure to her neck, Miriam’s fingers clamp down on her lips. Muffled screams are still heard. Darn, this would not do at all! <br>
<br>
“Say ah!” Miriam lets go and is answered by another scream. How fun. Reaching into Caru’s mouth, Miriam pulls out her tongue. <br>
<br>
“This * should * work. Now just hold still and it’ll all be over, hun” As gruesome as it may seem, Miriam slices off Caru’s tongue in a single motion. <br>
<br>
“Ta-da!” Now, rather than a scream, some odd sounding pain filled noise was being projected from that damned mouth of hers still. Fiddle sticks! Oo, oo! It would work now! Pressing both lips together for a second time, Miriam is able to successfully sew a row of delightful little x’s across Caru’s mouth. The amount of blood that spilled from her eyes alone was amazing. It made quite a nice puddle at her feet. Caru’s struggles came weaker and weaker as each second ticked by.<br>
<br>
“Hold on, sweetheart, almost done” Miriam’s voice was soothing like a Mother telling her child that soon the scrape on the knee would be bound. Well lookie here! The @#%$ dagger was still clean! Tisk tisk, this would not do, not do at all! Clutching onto Caru’s shirt, Miriam hold’s her up just long enough to lop off both ears. <br>
<br>
“That wasn’t so bad, was it?” Miriam gave her head a quick pat before her body fell over. Skipping happily she makes her way out of the town gates. The small bag she swung in her hand was soaked and dripped something other than water.<br>
